ing plan:\\n\\n# Plan: Add `entire trail enable` / `entire trail disable`\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nThe `entire trail` command was just implemented but lacks enable/disable subcommands. Users need a way to opt out of trail auto-creation and pushing. The feature should be enabled by default but togglable via settings.\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nStore a `trails` boolean in `StrategyOptions` (same pattern as `push_sessions`). Default: enabled (true). When disabled, skip auto-create on session start and skip pushing the trails branch.\\n\\n## Implementation Steps\\n\\n### 1. Add settings convenience functions\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/settings/settings.go`\\n\\nAdd `IsTrailsDisabled()` method on `*EntireSettings` — follows the `IsPushSessionsDisabled()` pattern exactly:\\n```go\\nfunc (s *EntireSettings) IsTrailsDisabled() bool {\\n    // Check StrategyOptions[\\\"trails\\\"] — false means disabled\\n    // Missing/nil means enabled (default)\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdd package-level convenience:\\n```go\\nfunc IsTrailsDisabled() bool {\\n    s, err := Load()\\n    if err != nil { return false }\\n    return s.IsTrailsDisabled()\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 2. Add `enable` and `disable` subcommands\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go`\\n\\nAdd to `newTrailCmd()`:\\n```\\ncmd.AddCommand(newTrailEnableCmd())\\ncmd.AddCommand(newTrailDisableCmd())\\n```\\n\\n`entire trail enable` — sets `strategy_options.trails = true` (or removes the key since true is default). Saves to project settings.\\n\\n`entire trail disable` — sets `strategy_options.trails = false`. Saves to local settings by default, `--project` flag for project settings.\\n\\nFollow the pattern from `setup.go` `runEnable`/`runDisable` — load settings, modify `StrategyOptions`, save.\\n\\n### 3. Guard auto-create with settings check\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go` — `autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart()`\\n\\nAdd at the top:\\n```go\\nif settings.IsTrailsDisabled() {\\n    return\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 4. Guard push with settings check\\