ire/trails` branch (similar to checkpoints)\\n+- One trail per branch - trail tracks the full lifecycle of work on that branch\\n+- Link to checkpoints via branch name matching (`trail.branch === checkpoint.branch`)\\n+- Support discussion/comments stored alongside trail metadata\\n+- Sync trails to database for fast querying (same pattern as checkpoints)\\n+- No dependency on GitHub PRs - PR info is optional/supplementary\\n+\\n+## Concepts\\n+\\n+### Trail Lifecycle\\n+\\n+```\\n+draft → open → in_progress → in_review → done → closed\\n+  │                              │           │\\n+  │   work happening             │  merged   │  abandoned\\n+  └──────────────────────────────┴───────────┴──────────\\n+```\\n+\\n+### Relationship Model\\n+\\n+```\\n+Trail (1) ←──branch──→ (many) Checkpoints\\n+   │                         │\\n+   └── \\\"why/what\\\"            └── \\\"how/when\\\"\\n+       (human intent)            (machine snapshots)\\n+```\\n+\\n+- **Trail**: Human-defined work item tracking purpose and status\\n+- **Checkpoint**: Machine-generated snapshot of work at a commit\\n+- **Link**: `trail.branch === checkpoint.branch` (no explicit foreign key needed)\\n+\\n+## Storage Format\\n+\\n+### Branch Structure\\n+\\n+```\\n+entire/trails/\\n+├── ab/\\n+│   └── cdef123456/              # trail_id (first 2 chars / rest)\\n+│       ├── metadata.json        # trail metadata\\n+│       └── discussion.json      # comments/threads\\n+├── de/\\n+│   └── f789abcdef/\\n+│       ├── metadata.json\\n+│       └── discussion.json\\n+```\\n+\\n+### metadata.json\\n+\\n+```json\\n+{\\n+  \\\"trail_id\\\": \\\"abcdef123456\\\",\\n+  \\\"branch\\\": \\\"feature/auth\\\",\\n+  \\\"base\\\": \\\"main\\\",\\n+\\n+  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Add user authentication\\\",\\n+  \\\"description\\\": \\\"Implement OAuth2 login with GitHub provider.\\\\nIncludes session management and token refresh.\\\",\\n+\\n+  \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress\\\",\\n+  \\\"author\\\": \\\"alice\\\",\\n+  