e carry-forward checkpoint.\\n  1890→\\t// CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0 is intentional: each checkpoint is self-contained with\\n  1891→\\t// the full transcript. This trades storage efficiency for simplicity:\\n  1892→\\t// - Pro: Each checkpoint is independently readable without needing to stitch together\\n  1893→\\t//   multiple checkpoints to understand the session history\\n  1894→\\t// - Con: For long sessions with multiple partial commits, each checkpoint includes\\n  1895→\\t//   the full transcript, which could be large\\n  1896→\\t// An alternative would be incremental checkpoints (only new content since last condensation),\\n  1897→\\t// but this would complicate checkpoint retrieval and require careful tracking of dependencies.\\n  1898→\\tstate.StepCount = 1\\n  1899→\\tstate.CheckpointTranscriptStart = 0\\n  1900→\\tstate.LastCheckpointID = \\\"\\\"\\n  1901→\\t// NOTE: TurnCheckpointIDs is intentionally NOT cleared here. Those checkpoint\\n  1902→\\t// IDs from earlier in the turn still need finalization with the full transcript\\n  1903→\\t// when HandleTurnEnd runs at stop time.\\n  1904→\\n  1905→\\tlogging.Info(logCtx, \\\"post-commit: carried forward remaining files\\\",\\n  1906→\\t\\tslog.String(\\\"session_id\\\", state.SessionID),\\n  1907→\\t\\tslog.Int(\\\"remaining_files\\\", len(remainingFiles)),\\n  1908→\\t)\\n  1909→}\\n  1910→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"bd0a6608-09b3-48f0-a957-575d2edb5dd8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-20T17:48:13.766Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"I need to understand two things about the trail system in this CLI:\\n\\n1. **checkpoints.json for trails**: The web app (PR entirehq/entire.io#738) expects each trail to have a `checkpoints.json` file alongside `metadata.json` and `discussion.json` on the `entire/trails` branch. Format:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"checkpoints\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"xyz789\\\",\\n      \\\"commit_sha\\\": \\\"abc123def456\\\",\\n      \\\"crea