ead.Hash(), sessionData.Prompts)\\n```\\n\\nAdd helper function (in `manual_commit_hooks.go` or a new `trail_link.go` in strategy):\\n```go\\nfunc appendCheckpointToTrail(repo *git.Repository, cpID id.CheckpointID, commitSHA plumbing.Hash, prompts []string) {\\n    branchName := GetCurrentBranchName(repo)\\n    if branchName == \\\"\\\" || isDefaultBranch(repo, branchName) {\\n        return\\n    }\\n    store := trail.NewStore(repo)\\n    existing, err := store.FindByBranch(branchName)\\n    if err != nil || existing == nil {\\n        return // No trail for this branch\\n    }\\n    summary := \\\"\\\"\\n    if len(prompts) > 0 {\\n        summary = truncateString(prompts[len(prompts)-1], 200)\\n    }\\n    ref := trail.CheckpointRef{\\n        CheckpointID: cpID.String(),\\n        CommitSHA:    commitSHA.String(),\\n        CreatedAt:    time.Now().UTC(),\\n        Summary:      summary,\\n    }\\n    store.AddCheckpoint(existing.TrailID, ref) // best-effort, don't fail condensation\\n}\\n```\\n\\nNote: `sessionData.Prompts` is available in `condenseAndUpdateState` — need to pass it through. Currently the method signature is:\\n```go\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) condenseAndUpdateState(logCtx, repo, checkpointID, state, head, shadowBranchName, shadowBranchesToDelete, committedFiles)\\n```\\nThe `CondenseSession` return doesn't include prompts, but `CondenseSession` has them internally via `sessionData.Prompts`. Options:\\n- Add `Prompts []string` to `CondenseResult` (cleanest)\\n- Or have `appendCheckpointToTrail` take no summary (simpler, summary can be added later)\\n\\n**Decision**: Add `Prompts` to `CondenseResult` — it's already computed and useful.\\n\\n### 3. Append checkpoint ref on save (auto-commit)\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/auto_commit.go`\\n\\nIn `SaveStep()`, after successful metadata commit (after line 163), add same trail linking:\\n```go\\nappendCheckpointToTrail(repo, cpID, codeResult.CommitHash, ctx./* prompts or commit message */)\\n```\\n\\nFor auto-commit, the `StepContext` doesn't have extracted prompts directly. Use `ctx.CommitMessage` as the summary instead.\\n\\n### 4. Pass prompt to trail auto-creation for semantic titles\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/lifecycle.go`\\n\\nChange `autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart()` to accept prompt:\\n```go\\n// Line 149: pass event.Prompt\\nautoCreateTrailOnTurnStart(event.Prompt)\\n\\n// Updated signature\\nfunc autoCreateTrailOnTurnStart(prompt string) {\\n```\\n\\nPass prompt through to `AutoCreateTrail`:\\n```go\\nAutoCreateTrail(repo, branchName, baseBranch, prompt)\\n```\\n\\n**File**: `cmd/entire/cli/trail_cmd.go`\\n\\nUpdate `AutoCreateTrail` signature:\\n```go\\nfunc AutoCreateTrail(repo *git.Repository, branchName, baseBranch, prompt string) error {\\n```\\n\\nUse prompt for title:\\n```go\\ntitle := titleFromPrompt(prompt)\\nif title == \\\"\\\" {\\n    title = trail.HumanizeBranchName(branchName) // fallback\\n}\\n```\\n\\nAdd helper:\\n```go\\nfunc titleFromPrompt(prompt string) string {\\n    if prompt == \\\"\\\" {\\n        return \\\"\\\"\\n    }\\n    // Take first line, trim, truncate to 80 chars\\n    line, _, _ := strings.Cut(prompt, \\\"\\\\n\\\")\\n    title := strings.TrimSpace(line)\\n    if len(title) > 80 {\\n        title = title[:77] + \\\"...\\\"\\n    }\\n    return title\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Update CLAUDE.md\\n\\nDocument `checkpoints.json` storage format and the prompt-based title generation.\\n\\n## Files Summary\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/trail/trail.go` | Add `CheckpointRef`, `Checkpoints` types |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/trail/store.go` | Add `checkpoints.json` to Write/Read, add `AddCheckpoint()` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` | Call `appendCheckpointToTrail` after condensation |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_types.go` | Add `Prompts` to `CondenseResult` |\\n| `cmd/entire/cli/strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` | Populate `Prompts` in result |